      <h1 class='title'>Renewable Energy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 cc247-8WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_247ws' title='Col. 247WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c247WS' name='column_247ws' href='#column_247ws' rel='bookmark'>247WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06165'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_195'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/dr-vincent-cable' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_195' title='Link to this speech by Dr Vincent Cable' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/dr-vincent-cable" title="Dr Vincent Cable">Dr. Cable</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06165">To ask the Secretary of State for Trade and Industry what discussions she has had with ministerial colleagues on the potential impact on the development of renewable energy sources of the implementation of an indicative planning process; and if she will make a statement. [88050]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06166'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_196'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-brian-wilson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_196' title='Link to this speech by Mr Brian Wilson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-brian-wilson" title="Mr Brian Wilson">Mr. Wilson</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06166"> <span class="italic">[holding answer 19 December 2002]:</span> DTI Ministers have met and discussed the impact of renewable energy developments on the planning process with colleagues in the Office of the Deputy Prime Minister. These discussions have taken place in the context of: preparing the Energy White Paper, which the Government plan to publish early in the new year, the re-drafting of Planning Policy Statement 22 which sets out statutory planning guidance on renewables in England and the ODPM's wider planning reforms.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_248ws' title='Col. 248WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c248WS' name='column_248ws' href='#column_248ws' rel='bookmark'>248WS</a>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
